					<description><![CDATA[<p>Researchers are leading the nation in developing powerful and precise radiopharmaceutical theranostics intended to treat people with deadly cancers. &amp;#160; ROCHESTER, Minn. — Mayo Clinic recently became the first institution to administer an investigational radioactive medicine to a patient with hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC), the most common type of liver cancer. The investigational medicine is a [&amp;#8230;]</p>
